1
00:00:07,541 --> 00:00:12,458
[opening theme music playing]

2
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:21,250
[electronic chirp]

3
00:00:23,333 --> 00:00:26,250
[electronic warbling]

4
00:00:35,291 --> 00:00:40,125
[emcee] Lords and Ladies of the Empire,
welcome!

5
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:46,500
[dramatically] Space,
once an unreachable frontier,

6
00:00:47,208 --> 00:00:50,791
is now a dazzling playground
for Earth's children.

7
00:00:52,291 --> 00:00:58,582
And so, we gather here,
above the frozen skies of Jupiter...

8
00:00:58,583 --> 00:00:59,499
[crowd cheering]

9
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:02,708
...to witness the sacred union

10
00:01:03,708 --> 00:01:06,249
of our glorious regent,

11
00:01:06,250 --> 00:01:08,958
Lord Chalon of Europa,

12
00:01:09,666 --> 00:01:12,958
and the Duchess Saraka of Callisto.

13
00:01:13,458 --> 00:01:14,999
[all chuckling]

14
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:19,583
Their love must be tempered
with ritual and ceremony,

15
00:01:20,125 --> 00:01:23,375
shaped in the crucible of chaos...

16
00:01:24,166 --> 00:01:25,957
- [woman chuckles]
- [glasses clink]

17
00:01:25,958 --> 00:01:29,416
...and sanctified with blood,

18
00:01:30,708 --> 00:01:35,707
blood spilled in tribute
on these sands below.

19
00:01:35,708 --> 00:01:37,290
[dramatic music playing]

20
00:01:37,291 --> 00:01:41,541
Tonight, you will witness
a spectacle like no other.

21
00:01:43,583 --> 00:01:46,082
Behold the riders.

22
00:01:46,083 --> 00:01:47,916
[crowd cheering]

23
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:51,999
[emcee] Are they not
absolutely magnificent?

24
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,833
[indistinct chatter]

25
00:01:54,541 --> 00:01:57,124
[emcee] Years of discipline and training

26
00:01:57,125 --> 00:02:02,000
have forged them into the perfect warriors
you see before you.

27
00:02:02,541 --> 00:02:03,790
[grunting]

28
00:02:03,791 --> 00:02:06,832
[emcee] Champions honed to a razor's edge,

29
00:02:06,833 --> 00:02:12,041
each blessed with the strength
and ferocity of their totem spirit.

30
00:02:12,833 --> 00:02:15,833
[woman 1 in Mandarin] <i>My sigil
marks me as wild and untamed.</i>

31
00:02:16,875 --> 00:02:21,665
<i>It is a secret prayer,
my longing to be free.</i>

32
00:02:21,666 --> 00:02:23,999
[pensive music playing]

33
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:26,250
[in English] To those
who are about to die,

34
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:28,083
we salute you.

35
00:02:28,916 --> 00:02:30,457
[horn blares]

36
00:02:30,458 --> 00:02:31,707
[woman 2 growls]

37
00:02:31,708 --> 00:02:34,165
- [drums beating]
- [breathes steadily]

38
00:02:34,166 --> 00:02:37,165
Now let the race begin!

39
00:02:37,166 --> 00:02:39,749
- [growling]
- [action music playing]

40
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:41,165
[all grunt]

41
00:02:41,166 --> 00:02:42,625
[panting]

42
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:47,333
[triceratops bellowing]

43
00:02:49,166 --> 00:02:50,166
[grunts]

44
00:02:51,541 --> 00:02:52,874
- [grunts]
- [clinks]

45
00:02:52,875 --> 00:02:55,499
[straining]

46
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:57,874
[shouts, grunts]

47
00:02:57,875 --> 00:02:59,082
[grunts]

48
00:02:59,083 --> 00:03:02,665
[whirring]

49
00:03:02,666 --> 00:03:07,332
- [crowd cheering]
- [suspenseful music playing]

50
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:09,333
[spacecraft whirs]

51
00:03:14,666 --> 00:03:15,916
[grunts]

52
00:03:16,458 --> 00:03:17,750
- [screams]
- [grunts]

53
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:21,582
[woman chuckles]

54
00:03:21,583 --> 00:03:23,207
[cheering]

55
00:03:23,208 --> 00:03:25,750
[dramatic music playing]

56
00:03:26,625 --> 00:03:28,083
[triceratops bellows]

57
00:03:29,583 --> 00:03:31,416
[panting]

58
00:03:32,125 --> 00:03:33,000
[grunts]

59
00:03:34,041 --> 00:03:35,999
[triceratops growling]

60
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,124
[energy pulses]

61
00:03:37,125 --> 00:03:39,457
[in Mandarin] <i>Everything
that does not please our overlords</i>

62
00:03:39,458 --> 00:03:40,707
<i>has been stripped away.</i>

63
00:03:40,708 --> 00:03:47,208
<i>In the darkness above Europa,
they take everything from us.</i>

64
00:03:47,708 --> 00:03:48,916
[breathing heavily]

65
00:03:49,916 --> 00:03:52,666
[grunting]

66
00:03:55,458 --> 00:03:57,375
[gasps, grunts]

67
00:04:00,083 --> 00:04:02,083
[both grunting]

68
00:04:08,250 --> 00:04:10,500
[yelps, screams]

69
00:04:11,083 --> 00:04:14,082
[grunting]

70
00:04:14,083 --> 00:04:17,041
[dramatic music continues]

71
00:04:18,291 --> 00:04:19,457
[growling]

72
00:04:19,458 --> 00:04:21,500
[grunting]

73
00:04:23,291 --> 00:04:24,375
[grunts]

74
00:04:25,541 --> 00:04:26,957
[groans, grunts]

75
00:04:26,958 --> 00:04:27,875
[screams]

76
00:04:29,416 --> 00:04:30,875
[triceratops bellows]

77
00:04:33,125 --> 00:04:36,915
[dramatic music continues]

78
00:04:36,916 --> 00:04:41,333
[woman] <i>A wolf alone can be outrun,
out-fought, out-maneuvered.</i>

79
00:04:41,916 --> 00:04:43,833
[howling]

80
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:50,875
[woman] <i>But the wolf pack
is an apex predator.</i>

81
00:04:53,708 --> 00:04:55,708
[dramatic music crescendos]

82
00:04:57,166 --> 00:04:58,833
[grunting]

83
00:04:59,916 --> 00:05:00,875
[grunts]

84
00:05:01,375 --> 00:05:02,958
- [grapple whistles]
- [grunts]

85
00:05:03,625 --> 00:05:04,832
[bellows]

86
00:05:04,833 --> 00:05:05,916
[grunts]

87
00:05:06,416 --> 00:05:07,916
[shouting]

88
00:05:10,875 --> 00:05:12,125
[grunting]

89
00:05:14,166 --> 00:05:15,082
[man groans]

90
00:05:15,083 --> 00:05:16,125
[both grunt]

91
00:05:18,666 --> 00:05:19,750
[spacecraft whirs]

92
00:05:26,916 --> 00:05:28,750
[grunts, strains]

93
00:05:31,541 --> 00:05:32,666
[triceratops growls]

94
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:35,874
[grapple whistling]

95
00:05:35,875 --> 00:05:36,791
[grunts]

96
00:05:38,875 --> 00:05:40,750
- [shouts]
- [bellows]

97
00:05:41,791 --> 00:05:42,708
[grunts]

98
00:05:43,583 --> 00:05:45,166
[both grunting]

99
00:05:47,250 --> 00:05:50,082
[screaming]

100
00:05:50,083 --> 00:05:51,457
[triceratops groans]

101
00:05:51,458 --> 00:05:54,041
- [ground rumbles]
- [crowd cheering]

102
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:57,000
[breathing heavily]

103
00:05:57,583 --> 00:05:58,999
[spacecraft whirs]

104
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,499
[cheering continues]

105
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,582
[in English] Yeah!

106
00:06:02,583 --> 00:06:06,666
[suspenseful music playing]

107
00:06:08,291 --> 00:06:11,625
[woman in Mandarin] <i>The aristocracy
mate for money and power.</i>

108
00:06:13,083 --> 00:06:18,665
<i>But we who can own nothing...</i>

109
00:06:18,666 --> 00:06:19,582
[energy pulses]

110
00:06:19,583 --> 00:06:23,500
...<i>have something real,
something primal, something true.</i>

111
00:06:25,250 --> 00:06:26,625
[dramatic music builds]

112
00:06:27,208 --> 00:06:28,790
[shouts]

113
00:06:28,791 --> 00:06:32,082
[both grunting]

114
00:06:32,083 --> 00:06:33,416
[triceratops growls]

115
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:38,583
- [grunts]
- [blade rings]

116
00:06:39,291 --> 00:06:42,083
[dramatic music continues]

117
00:06:42,666 --> 00:06:43,666
[grunts]

118
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,166
[grunt echoes]

119
00:06:52,875 --> 00:06:54,291
[grunts]

120
00:06:58,041 --> 00:06:59,749
[woman] <i>She is magnificent.</i>

121
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:00,958
[energy pulses]

122
00:07:02,125 --> 00:07:04,499
- [grunts]
- [triceratops groans]

123
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:06,832
[woman strains]

124
00:07:06,833 --> 00:07:09,333
- [music fades]
- [crowd cheering]

125
00:07:09,958 --> 00:07:11,207
[in English] Whoo! Yeah.

126
00:07:11,208 --> 00:07:12,291
[glasses clink]

127
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,000
[cheering continues]

128
00:07:17,375 --> 00:07:21,125
[dramatic music playing]

129
00:07:21,708 --> 00:07:24,082
Was that not glorious?

130
00:07:24,083 --> 00:07:29,083
A contest of heroes
worthy of this celestial union.

131
00:07:30,208 --> 00:07:33,666
But for this most special occasion,

132
00:07:34,166 --> 00:07:35,958
we have something more,

133
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:39,915
a final challenge to test our champion

134
00:07:39,916 --> 00:07:43,999
against nature's most
savagely primal creation.

135
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,457
[eerie music playing]

136
00:07:46,458 --> 00:07:48,374
[metal creaks]

137
00:07:48,375 --> 00:07:50,166
[breath wavering]

138
00:07:53,291 --> 00:07:54,540
[roars]

139
00:07:54,541 --> 00:07:55,457
[in Mandarin] Fuck!

140
00:07:55,458 --> 00:07:58,291
[roaring]

141
00:07:59,375 --> 00:08:00,833
- [grunts]
- [roars]

142
00:08:06,083 --> 00:08:08,457
[roaring]

143
00:08:08,458 --> 00:08:10,332
[shouts]

144
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:11,500
[strains]

145
00:08:12,750 --> 00:08:13,958
[grunting]

146
00:08:14,541 --> 00:08:16,666
[roaring]

147
00:08:17,541 --> 00:08:18,666
[bellows]

148
00:08:22,208 --> 00:08:24,333
- [air whooshes]
- [triceratops grumbles]

149
00:08:25,208 --> 00:08:26,541
- [woman shouts]
- [roars]

150
00:08:27,208 --> 00:08:28,332
[growls]

151
00:08:28,333 --> 00:08:29,582
[strains]

152
00:08:29,583 --> 00:08:30,958
[dinosaurs roar]

153
00:08:31,958 --> 00:08:32,915
[woman grunts]

154
00:08:32,916 --> 00:08:34,125
[flesh tearing]

155
00:08:34,708 --> 00:08:38,249
Turn! You big bastard!

156
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:40,333
[dramatic music playing]

157
00:08:41,708 --> 00:08:42,749
[roars]

158
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:44,541
- [shouts]
- [grunts]

159
00:08:45,958 --> 00:08:46,916
[grunts]

160
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:49,207
[shrieks]

161
00:08:49,208 --> 00:08:50,250
[strains]

162
00:08:51,208 --> 00:08:53,499
[roaring]

163
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:54,416
[woman shouts]

164
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:57,707
[grunting]

165
00:08:57,708 --> 00:09:00,374
[music fades]

166
00:09:00,375 --> 00:09:02,583
[groans weakly]

167
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:07,541
[wailing]

168
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:10,833
[crowd cheering]

169
00:09:15,708 --> 00:09:18,457
[cheering emphatically]

170
00:09:18,458 --> 00:09:20,333
[ominous music playing]

171
00:09:25,041 --> 00:09:27,041
[breathing weakly]

172
00:09:27,708 --> 00:09:29,291
[whirring]

173
00:09:31,166 --> 00:09:34,624
[emcee in English] My lords,
this carnage is no end...

174
00:09:34,625 --> 00:09:37,083
- [grunts]
- [emcee] It is a beginning.

175
00:09:38,583 --> 00:09:42,374
This King of the ancient world
gives us the gift

176
00:09:42,375 --> 00:09:44,583
of his matchless vitality.

177
00:09:45,458 --> 00:09:48,999
In his veins flows the power primordial...

178
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:52,624
as it will now flow
into those of our sovereigns,

179
00:09:52,625 --> 00:09:56,625
so that they may write
our future in blood.

180
00:09:57,916 --> 00:10:00,624
[in Mandarin] The Tyrannosaur
no longer screams.

181
00:10:00,625 --> 00:10:02,958
He has had his fill of blood.

182
00:10:05,041 --> 00:10:07,333
But you up there...

183
00:10:09,583 --> 00:10:11,124
[indistinct chatter]

184
00:10:11,125 --> 00:10:14,083
[woman] ...you will never have enough.

185
00:10:15,541 --> 00:10:21,666
Come... let us end this our way.

186
00:10:22,375 --> 00:10:23,540
[roars]

187
00:10:23,541 --> 00:10:24,791
[dramatic music rises]

188
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:37,749
[crowd screams]

189
00:10:37,750 --> 00:10:38,916
[Saraka shrieks]

190
00:10:40,666 --> 00:10:41,832
[tyrannosaur growls]

191
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:44,291
[Saraka screams]

192
00:10:47,916 --> 00:10:50,624
[screaming]

193
00:10:50,625 --> 00:10:51,540
[Chalon yelps]

194
00:10:51,541 --> 00:10:53,625
[music fades]

195
00:10:58,041 --> 00:10:59,165
[dramatic sting]

196
00:10:59,166 --> 00:11:01,166
- [grunts]
- [screams, grunts]

197
00:11:05,833 --> 00:11:08,500
[woman] <i>In the darkness above Europa...</i>

198
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:10,665
[grunting weakly]

199
00:11:10,666 --> 00:11:13,083
<i>...they take everything from us,</i>

200
00:11:13,958 --> 00:11:16,375
<i>even our memories.</i>

201
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:21,290
<i>Yet some fragments linger...</i>

202
00:11:21,291 --> 00:11:22,415
[tyrannosaur moans]

203
00:11:22,416 --> 00:11:25,458
[woman] <i>...like the last leaves of autumn.</i>

204
00:11:26,416 --> 00:11:29,499
<i>Among the blossoms,</i>

205
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:33,458
<i>I am alone with my wine.</i>

206
00:11:34,916 --> 00:11:38,750
<i>Lifting my cup,
I ask the moon to drink with me.</i>

207
00:11:40,583 --> 00:11:45,916
<i>Its reflection in the wine,
with mine, just we three.</i>

208
00:11:46,625 --> 00:11:47,999
[poignant music playing]

209
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:50,083
[wolves barking]

210
00:11:53,583 --> 00:11:57,791
[wolf howling]

211
00:12:00,375 --> 00:12:03,374
[music fades]

212
00:12:03,375 --> 00:12:07,958
[electronic warbling]

213
00:12:10,041 --> 00:12:13,958
[somber music playing]

214
00:13:36,041 --> 00:13:37,958
[music fades]

